{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1,"text":"What I do is I organize information."},{"time":1809,"text":"I'm a graphic designer."},{"time":3566,"text":"Professionally, I try to make sense"},{"time":6309,"text":"often of things that don't\nmake much sense themselves."}]},{"cues":[{"time":9938,"text":"So my father might not understand\nwhat it is that I do for a living."},{"time":14076,"text":"His part of my ancestry has been farmers."},{"time":16353,"text":"He's part of this ethnic minority\ncalled the Pontic Greeks."},{"time":19980,"text":"They lived in Asia Minor\nand fled to Greece after a genocide"},{"time":24416,"text":"about a hundred years ago."},{"time":26574,"text":"And ever since that, migration\nhas somewhat been a theme in my family."},{"time":30847,"text":"My father moved to Germany,\nstudied there and married,"},{"time":35372,"text":"and as a result, I now have\nthis half-German brain,"},{"time":39824,"text":"with all the analytical thinking\nand that slightly dorky demeanor"},{"time":43206,"text":"that come with that."},{"time":45209,"text":"And of course it meant\nthat I was a foreigner in both countries,"},{"time":48319,"text":"and that of course made it pretty easy\nfor me to migrate as well,"},{"time":52693,"text":"in good family tradition, if you like."}]},{"cues":[{"time":55672,"text":"But of course, most journeys\nthat we undertake from day to day"},{"time":59021,"text":"are within a city."},{"time":60671,"text":"And, especially if you know the city,"},{"time":63467,"text":"getting from A to B\nmay seem pretty obvious, right?"},{"time":68291,"text":"But the question is, why is it obvious?"},{"time":71641,"text":"How do we know where we're going?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":73983,"text":"So I washed up on a Dublin ferry port\nabout 12 years ago,"},{"time":77832,"text":"a professional foreigner, if you like,"},{"time":80248,"text":"and I'm sure you've all had\nthis experience before, yeah?"},{"time":83374,"text":"You arrive in a new city,"},{"time":85486,"text":"and your brain is trying\nto make sense of this new place."},{"time":89483,"text":"Once you find your base, your home,"},{"time":92885,"text":"you start to build this cognitive map\nof your environment."},{"time":97345,"text":"It's essentially this virtual map\nthat only exists in your brain."},{"time":101257,"text":"All animal species do it,"},{"time":103042,"text":"even though we all use\nslightly different tools."},{"time":106041,"text":"Us humans, of course, we don't move around\nmarking our territory by scent, like dogs."},{"time":112090,"text":"We don't run around emitting\nultrasonic squeaks, like bats."},{"time":117606,"text":"We just don't do that,"},{"time":119627,"text":"although a night in the Temple Bar\ndistrict can get pretty wild."}]},{"cues":[{"time":122897,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":124269,"text":"No, we do two important things\nto make a place our own."},{"time":128207,"text":"First, we move along linear routes."},{"time":131283,"text":"Typically, we find a main street,"},{"time":133777,"text":"and this main street becomes\na linear strip map in our minds."},{"time":137371,"text":"But our mind keeps it pretty simple, yeah?"},{"time":139618,"text":"Every street is generally perceived\nas a straight line,"},{"time":142997,"text":"and we kind of ignore the little twists\nand turns that the streets make."},{"time":147110,"text":"When we do, however,\nmake a turn into a side street,"},{"time":149584,"text":"our mind tends to adjust that turn\nto a 90-degree angle."},{"time":154898,"text":"This of course makes for\nsome funny moments"},{"time":157620,"text":"when you're in some old city layout"},{"time":159970,"text":"that follows some sort\nof circular city logic, yeah?"},{"time":164986,"text":"Maybe you've had that experience as well."}]},{"cues":[{"time":167098,"text":"Let's say you're on some spot\non a side street"},{"time":170218,"text":"that projects from a main\ncathedral square,"},{"time":172584,"text":"and you want to get to another point\non a side street just like that."},{"time":177308,"text":"The cognitive map\nin your mind may tell you,"},{"time":181278,"text":"\"Aris, go back to the main\ncathedral square,"},{"time":184703,"text":"take a 90-degree turn\nand walk down that other side street.\""},{"time":188440,"text":"But somehow you feel adventurous that day,\nand you suddenly discover"},{"time":192899,"text":"that the two spots were actually\nonly a single building apart."},{"time":197775,"text":"Now, I don't know about you,"},{"time":199140,"text":"but I always feel\nlike I find this wormhole"},{"time":201288,"text":"or this inter-dimensional portal."}]},{"cues":[{"time":204085,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":205383,"text":"So we move along linear routes"},{"time":208914,"text":"and our mind straightens streets\nand perceives turns as 90-degree angles."}]},{"cues":[{"time":214960,"text":"The second thing that we do\nto make a place our own"},{"time":217929,"text":"is we attach meaning\nand emotions to the things"},{"time":222116,"text":"that we see along those lines."},{"time":225005,"text":"If you go to the Irish countryside\nand you ask an old lady for directions,"},{"time":230896,"text":"brace yourself for some\nelaborate Irish storytelling"},{"time":234808,"text":"about all the landmarks, yeah?"},{"time":236786,"text":"She'll tell you the pub\nwhere her sister used to work,"},{"time":240061,"text":"and \"... go past that church\nwhere I got married,\" that kind of thing."},{"time":243456,"text":"So we fill our cognitive maps\nwith these markers of meaning."},{"time":248043,"text":"What's more, we abstract\nrepeat patterns and recognize them."},{"time":253694,"text":"We recognize them by the experiences\nand we abstract them into symbols."},{"time":259644,"text":"And of course, we're all capable\nof understanding these symbols."}]},{"cues":[{"time":264699,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":265759,"text":"What's more, we're all capable\nof understanding the cognitive maps,"},{"time":270266,"text":"and you are all capable of creating\nthese cognitive maps yourselves."},{"time":276008,"text":"So next time, when you want to tell\nyour friend how to get to your place,"},{"time":279625,"text":"you grab a beermat, grab a napkin,\nand you just observe yourself"},{"time":284417,"text":"create this awesome piece\nof communication design."},{"time":288808,"text":"It's got straight lines."},{"time":290244,"text":"It's got 90-degree corners."},{"time":292746,"text":"You might add little symbols\nalong the way."},{"time":294870,"text":"And when you look\nat what you've just drawn,"},{"time":299013,"text":"you realize it does not\nresemble a street map."},{"time":303575,"text":"If you were to put an actual street map\non top of what you've just drawn,"},{"time":307874,"text":"you'd realize your streets\nand the distances -- they'd be way off."},{"time":313220,"text":"No, what you've just drawn\nis more like a diagram or a schematic."},{"time":318856,"text":"It's a visual construct\nof lines, dots, letters,"},{"time":323827,"text":"designed in the language of our brains."}]},{"cues":[{"time":326719,"text":"So it's no big surprise"},{"time":328599,"text":"that the big information-design icon\nof the last century --"},{"time":333582,"text":"the pinnacle of showing everybody\nhow to get from A to B,"},{"time":337939,"text":"the London Underground map --"},{"time":339981,"text":"was not designed by a cartographer\nor a city planner;"},{"time":344318,"text":"it was designed\nby an engineering draftsman."},{"time":348714,"text":"In the 1930s,"},{"time":350448,"text":"Harry Beck applied the principles\nof schematic diagram design"},{"time":356624,"text":"and changed the way public transport\nmaps are designed forever."},{"time":361270,"text":"Now the very key\nto the success of this map"},{"time":364989,"text":"is in the omission\nof less important information"},{"time":369073,"text":"and in the extreme simplification."},{"time":371792,"text":"So, straightened streets,\ncorners of 90 and 45 degrees,"},{"time":375752,"text":"but also the extreme geographic\ndistortion in that map."},{"time":381896,"text":"If you were to look at the actual\nlocations of these stations,"},{"time":385826,"text":"you'd see they're very different."},{"time":388493,"text":"But this is all for the clarity\nof the public Tube map."},{"time":393081,"text":"If you, say, wanted to get\nfrom Regent's Park station"},{"time":396249,"text":"to Great Portland Street,"},{"time":397899,"text":"the Tube map would tell you:"},{"time":399757,"text":"take the Tube, go to Baker Street,\nchange over, take another Tube."},{"time":404393,"text":"Of course, what you don't know\nis that the two stations"},{"time":408314,"text":"are only about a hundred meters apart."}]},{"cues":[{"time":410882,"text":"Now we've reached the subject\nof public transport,"},{"time":413793,"text":"and public transport here in Dublin"},{"time":416861,"text":"is a somewhat touchy subject."}]},{"cues":[{"time":418868,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":421171,"text":"For everybody who does not know\nthe public transport here in Dublin,"},{"time":424408,"text":"essentially, we have this system\nof local buses that grew with the city."},{"time":429375,"text":"For every outskirt that was added,\nthere was another bus route added,"},{"time":433023,"text":"running from the outskirt\nall the way to the city center."},{"time":437967,"text":"And as these local buses\napproach the city center,"},{"time":441960,"text":"they all run side by side and converge\nin pretty much one main street."}]},{"cues":[{"time":447535,"text":"So when I stepped off\nthe boat 12 years ago,"},{"time":451472,"text":"I tried to make sense of that."},{"time":455557,"text":"Because exploring a city on foot\nonly gets you so far."},{"time":459974,"text":"But when you explore a foreign\nand new public transport system,"},{"time":465327,"text":"you will build a cognitive map\nin your mind in pretty much the same way."},{"time":471102,"text":"Typically, you choose yourself\na rapid transport route,"},{"time":475859,"text":"and in your mind, this route\nis perceived as a straight line."},{"time":480295,"text":"And like a pearl necklace,"},{"time":481971,"text":"all the stations and stops are nicely\nand neatly aligned along the line."},{"time":487589,"text":"And only then you start to discover\nsome local bus routes"},{"time":493267,"text":"that would fill in the gaps,"},{"time":495006,"text":"and that allow for those wormhole,\ninter-dimensional portal shortcuts."},{"time":501687,"text":"So I tried to make sense,\nand when I arrived,"},{"time":505103,"text":"I was looking for some\ninformation leaflets"},{"time":507667,"text":"that would help me crack this system\nand understand it,"},{"time":511208,"text":"and I found those brochures."}]},{"cues":[{"time":513373,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":517474,"text":"They were not geographically distorted."},{"time":520843,"text":"They had a lot of omission of information,"},{"time":524847,"text":"but unfortunately, the wrong information."},{"time":527238,"text":"Say, in the city center --"},{"time":529012,"text":"there were never actually any lines\nthat showed the routes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":532263,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":533431,"text":"There are actually not even\nany stations with names."}]},{"cues":[{"time":538205,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":539475,"text":"Now, the maps of Dublin transport\nhave gotten better,"},{"time":545122,"text":"and after I finished the project,\nthey got a good bit better,"},{"time":550312,"text":"but still no station names,\nstill no routes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":553375,"text":"So, being naive,\nand being half-German, I decided,"},{"time":559509,"text":"\"Aris, why don't you build your own map?\""},{"time":562612,"text":"So that's what I did."},{"time":563951,"text":"I researched how each and every bus route\nmoved through the city, nice and logical,"},{"time":569963,"text":"every bus route a separate line."},{"time":572678,"text":"I plotted it into my own map of Dublin,"},{"time":576059,"text":"and in the city center ..."},{"time":578670,"text":"I got a nice spaghetti plate."}]},{"cues":[{"time":580324,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":582876,"text":"Now, this is a bit of a mess,"},{"time":585949,"text":"so I decided, of course,"},{"time":588123,"text":"\"You're going to apply\nthe rules of schematic design,\""},{"time":591702,"text":"cleaning up the corridors,"},{"time":593587,"text":"widening the streets\nwhere there were loads of buses"},{"time":596366,"text":"and making the streets at straight,\n90-degree corners, 45-degree corners"},{"time":601175,"text":"or fractions of that,"},{"time":602628,"text":"and filled it in with the bus routes."},{"time":605638,"text":"And I built this city center\nbus map of the system,"},{"time":608961,"text":"how it was five years ago."},{"time":611350,"text":"I'll zoom in again\nso that you get the full impact"},{"time":613736,"text":"of the quays and Westmoreland Street."}]},{"cues":[{"time":616086,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":618777,"text":"Now I can proudly say --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":620791,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":627143,"text":"I can proudly say,\nas a public transport map,"},{"time":631348,"text":"this diagram is an utter failure."}]},{"cues":[{"time":635304,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":637215,"text":"Except, probably, in one aspect:"},{"time":639274,"text":"I now had a great visual representation"},{"time":641926,"text":"of just how clogged up and overrun\nthe city center really was."}]},{"cues":[{"time":646515,"text":"Now, call me old-fashioned,"},{"time":649171,"text":"but I think a public transport\nroute map should have lines,"},{"time":652678,"text":"because that's what they are, yeah?"},{"time":654795,"text":"They're little pieces of string\nthat wrap their way"},{"time":658035,"text":"through the city center\nor through the city."},{"time":660739,"text":"If you will, the Greek guy inside of me\nfeels if I don't get a line,"},{"time":666254,"text":"it's like entering\nthe labyrinth of the Minotaur"},{"time":669347,"text":"without having Ariadne giving you\nthe string to find your way."},{"time":672635,"text":"So the outcome of my academic research,"},{"time":676602,"text":"loads of questionnaires, case studies\nand looking at a lot of maps,"},{"time":683399,"text":"was that a lot of the problems\nand shortcomings"},{"time":685836,"text":"of the public transport\nsystem here in Dublin"},{"time":688182,"text":"was the lack of a coherent\npublic transport map --"},{"time":690612,"text":"a simplified, coherent\npublic transport map --"},{"time":693353,"text":"because I think this is the crucial\nstep to understanding"},{"time":696792,"text":"a public transport network\non a physical level,"},{"time":700013,"text":"but it's also the crucial step to make\na public transport network mappable"},{"time":704332,"text":"on a visual level."}]},{"cues":[{"time":706339,"text":"So I teamed up with a gentleman\ncalled James Leahy,"},{"time":710273,"text":"a civil engineer and a recent\nmaster's graduate"},{"time":713608,"text":"of the Sustainable Development\nprogram at DIT,"},{"time":716942,"text":"and together we drafted\nthe simplified model network,"},{"time":721269,"text":"which I could then go ahead and visualize."}]},{"cues":[{"time":724571,"text":"So here's what we did."},{"time":726626,"text":"We distributed these rapid-transport\ncorridors throughout the city center,"},{"time":732940,"text":"and extended them into the outskirts."},{"time":735840,"text":"Rapid, because we wanted them to be served\nby rapid-transport vehicles."},{"time":742055,"text":"They would get exclusive\nroad use, where possible,"},{"time":745989,"text":"and it would be high-quantity,\nhigh-quality transport."},{"time":748568,"text":"James wanted to use\nbus rapid transport for that,"},{"time":751270,"text":"rather than light rail."},{"time":752724,"text":"For me, it was important"},{"time":754875,"text":"that the vehicles that would run\non those rapid transport corridors"},{"time":759297,"text":"would be visibly distinguishable\nfrom local buses on the street."},{"time":764713,"text":"Now we could take out all the local buses"},{"time":767779,"text":"that ran alongside\nthose rapid transport means."},{"time":770876,"text":"Any gaps that appeared\nin the outskirts were filled again."},{"time":774392,"text":"So, in other words,\nif there was a street in an outskirt"},{"time":777629,"text":"where there had been a bus,\nwe put a bus back in,"},{"time":780716,"text":"only now these buses wouldn't run\nall the way to the city center,"},{"time":785171,"text":"but connect to the nearest\nrapid-transport mode,"},{"time":788735,"text":"one of these thick lines over there."},{"time":790920,"text":"So the rest was merely\na couple of months of work,"},{"time":794089,"text":"and a couple of fights with my girlfriend,"},{"time":796212,"text":"of our place constantly\nbeing clogged up with maps,"},{"time":800188,"text":"and the outcome, one of the outcomes,"},{"time":802205,"text":"was this map of the Greater Dublin area."},{"time":805462,"text":"I'll zoom in a little bit."}]},{"cues":[{"time":808548,"text":"This map only shows the rapid\ntransport connections, no local bus,"},{"time":812619,"text":"very much in the \"metro map\" style\nthat was so successful in London,"},{"time":817893,"text":"and that since has been exported\nto so many other major cities,"},{"time":822189,"text":"and therefore is the language\nthat we should use"},{"time":824994,"text":"for public transport maps."},{"time":827863,"text":"What's also important is,\nwith a simplified network like this,"},{"time":833404,"text":"it now would become possible for me\nto tackle the ultimate challenge"},{"time":838906,"text":"and make a public transport map\nfor the city center,"},{"time":842503,"text":"one where I wouldn't just show\nrapid transport connections,"},{"time":845623,"text":"but also all the local bus routes,\nstreets and the likes,"},{"time":849121,"text":"and this is what a map\nlike this could look like."},{"time":851455,"text":"I'll zoom in a little bit."}]},{"cues":[{"time":855926,"text":"In this map, I'm including\neach transport mode,"},{"time":860992,"text":"so rapid transport, bus,\nDART, tram and the likes."},{"time":866199,"text":"Each individual route\nis represented by a separate line."},{"time":873233,"text":"The map shows each and every station,"},{"time":877413,"text":"each and every station name,"},{"time":880742,"text":"and I'm also displaying side streets."},{"time":885516,"text":"In fact, most of the side streets\neven with their name,"},{"time":889021,"text":"and for good measure,\nalso a couple of landmarks,"},{"time":893972,"text":"some of them signified by little symbols,"},{"time":896170,"text":"others by these isometric\nthree-dimensional"},{"time":899283,"text":"bird's-eye-view drawings."}]},{"cues":[{"time":901305,"text":"The map is relatively small\nin overall size,"},{"time":903962,"text":"so something that you could\nstill hold as a fold-out map"},{"time":907127,"text":"or display in a reasonably-sized\ndisplay box on a bus shelter."},{"time":910809,"text":"I think it tries to be the best balance"},{"time":915477,"text":"between actual representation\nand simplification --"},{"time":918833,"text":"the language of way-finding in our brain."},{"time":924000,"text":"So, straightened lines,\ncleaned-up corners,"},{"time":927555,"text":"and of course, that very, very\nimportant geographic distortion"},{"time":931245,"text":"that makes public transport maps possible."},{"time":934793,"text":"If you, for example, have a look\nat the two main corridors"},{"time":937555,"text":"that run through the city --\nthe yellow and orange one over here --"},{"time":940851,"text":"this is how they look in an actual,\naccurate street map,"},{"time":944453,"text":"and this is how they would\nlook in my distorted,"},{"time":948462,"text":"simplified public transport map."}]},{"cues":[{"time":951416,"text":"So for a successful public transport map,"},{"time":954342,"text":"we should not stick\nto accurate representation,"},{"time":957120,"text":"but design them in the way\nour brains work."}]},{"cues":[{"time":959505,"text":"The reactions I got were tremendous,\nit was really good to see."},{"time":962800,"text":"And of course, for my own self,\nI was very happy to see"},{"time":966516,"text":"that my folks in Germany and Greece\nfinally have an idea"},{"time":969938,"text":"what I do for a living."}]},{"cues":[{"time":971141,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":972167,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":973342,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}